hudson
Class FilePath

java.lang.Object
  hudson.FilePath

public final class FilePath
extends java.lang.Object

File like path-manipulation object.

In general, because programs could be executed remotely, we need two path strings to identify the same directory. One from a point of view of the master (local), the other from a point of view of the slave (remote).

This class allows path manipulation to be done and allow the local/remote versions to be obtained after the computation.

Author:
Kohsuke Kawaguchi
